text: James Francis (1819–1884) was an Australian colonial politician. James Francis may also refer to: *James B. Francis (1815–1892), British-American engineer *James Francis (American football) (born 1968), former linebacker in the NFL *Jim Francis (1910–2004), Australian rules footballer and coach *James Francis, one of the members of the band Panic Lift ==See also== *
title: James Francis (disambiguation)
